- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)  
  **URL:** `https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “Phase 1 clinical trial evaluating **CT7439**, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (**CDK12/13**) inhibitor / **Cyclin-K glue-degrader**.”  
  - “advanced solid tumors, including **ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma**.”  
  - “under study ID: **NCT06600789**.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))

- **Title:** Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “development of **SR-4835**, a highly selective dual inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13**”  
  - “disables **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)** cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))

- **Title:** Novel CDK12/13 Inhibitors AU-15506 and AU-16770 Are Potent Anti-Cancer Agents in EGFR Mutant Lung Adenocarcinoma with and without Osimertinib Resistance (MDPI)  
  **URL:** `https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6694/15/8/2263`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “two novel **CDK12/13 inhibitors, AU-15506 and AU-16770**, in **osimertinib-resistant EGFR mutant lung adenocarcinoma**”  
  - “inhibition of **CDK12/13** in combination with **osimertinib** has the potential to overcome **osimertinib resistance**” ([mdpi.com](https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6694/15/8/2263))

- **Title:** Structure-activity relationship study of THZ531 derivatives enables the discovery of BSJ-01-175 as a dual CDK12/13 covalent inhibitor with efficacy in Ewing sarcoma (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33945934/`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “We previously described **THZ531**, a **covalent inhibitor** with selectivity for **CDK12/13**.”  
  - “**BSJ-01-175** exhibits efficacy against an **Ewing sarcoma** tumor growth in a patient-derived xenograft (**PDX**) mouse model” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33945934/))

- **Title:** Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “**PP-C8** demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with **PARP inhibitor** in **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)**.”  
  - “selective **CDK12 PROTAC degrader**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))

- **Title:** Discovery and design of molecular glue enhancers of CDK12–DDB1 interactions for targeted degradation of cyclin K (RSC Chemical Biology)  
  **URL:** `https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2024/cb/d4cb00190g`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “generate compound **MR-1226** (Fig. 5A). **MR-1226** effectively degraded cyclin K with a **DC _{50} of 50 nM**”  
  - “The **CDK12 inhibitor SR-4835** facilitates potent **molecular glue** activity enabling the degradation of cyclin K” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2024/cb/d4cb00190g))

- **Title:** EUB0001632a_CDK13 | EUbOPEN  
  **URL:** `https://www.eubopen.org/chemogenomics/chemogenomic-set/eub0001632acdk13`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “Compound name **SR-4835**”  
  - “Target name **CDK13**”  
  - “Compound EUbOPEN ID **EUB0001632a**” ([eubopen.org](https://www.eubopen.org/chemogenomics/chemogenomic-set/eub0001632acdk13))

- **Title:** WO2019217421A1 — Small molecule inhibitors of cdk12/cdk13 (Google Patents)  
  **URL:** `https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2019217421A1/en`  
  **Direct quote snippets:**  
  - “Publication number **WO2019217421A1**”  
  - “the only selective inhibitor of **CDK12/13** reported so far - **THZ531**”  
  - “use in targeted treatment of variety of cancers including **breast cancer**, **brain cancer** and **ovarian cancer**.” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2019217421A1/en))
